{"key":"post-6280118","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6280118</id>\n<content>You should consider three g2g transfers maximum.  I've even noticed slowing on the third transfer, but it isn't as big a decline as happens after that time.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The reason is that every organism including humans can only divide cells a finite number of times before degradation sets in.  In mushroom cultivation, we refer to this degradation as senescence.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I've written extensively here on the boards about senescence and ways to work around it to use the same culture for many years without it degrading.  Do a search under my user name for 'master culture slant' and or 'test tube' and you should find a bit of reading.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6280349</next>\n<prev>6280033</prev>\n<first>6278960</first>\n<last>6280349</last>\n<when>1163472017</when>\n<utime>11/14/06 04:40 AM</utime>\n</post>"}